  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Award Ceremony of the 2021 Edition of the UNESCO-Russia Mendeleev International Prize in the Basic Sciences</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Building on the success of the International Year of the Periodic Table of Chemical Elements (IYPT2019), the Government of the Russian Federation proposed to establish and fund the UNESCO/Russian Federation International Prize in the name of the Russian chemist Dmitry Mendeleev for the Basic Sciences. The Prize is awarded annually to two individuals for their breakthrough discoveries and for their dedicated promotion of basic science. Mendeleev Prize Award Ceremony of the 2021 Edition together with the side event exhibition at UNESCO HQs to celebrate the first laureates .</narrative>
  </description>
